If I could give zero stars to Bennys on ave J I would. They are the worst kosher pizza place in Brooklyn.  I have never left a bad review, but after the way I was treated today, I felt obligated to. When I arrived in the store I saw a fresh margarita pie in the display case so I decided to order a slice. When the slice came out of the oven the worker quickly put it into the box and handed it to me, hoping I wouldn't see. However, I saw, and I asked him respectfully if he could switch it out becuase it didn't look like the slice I ordered in the display case.  At first, he ignored me and after a few minutes of trying to get his attention, he started yelling at me and explaining how it was the same. After a couple of minutes of arguing he grabbed my box took the old slice out and put in a soggy cold new one. At this point, I just took the unedible pizza and left. I was not able to eat this slice and I ended up throwing it out. I would not recommend going to this establishment, I would walk down the block and go to one of the other pizza places.

IF NOT FOR THEIR FOOD THEY WOULD CLOSE DOWN IN ONE DAY!That being said their food is definitely different than you'd expect. Very nice touch and spin on pizza. Many slices are extra thick crust and seem to be on some type of focaccia breading. Delicious! Prices are almost double than regular pizza but whether it's worth it is debatable. ONLY problem is staff is definitely not friendly. I would say they can get down right nasty and will start getting frustrated or let out groans if you ask for extra like sauces or bags, just regular questions, basically just for things that one would assume are part of their job.  It's not uncommon for them to ignore a customer and then snap when you repeat yourself. They will make no bones about letting you know they are pissed and miserable. You gotta be a little thick skinned if you want a thick slice!
